---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — DearSQL"
  description="DearSQL privacy policy. We collect minimal data and never sell it."
>
  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-6 text-sm">
    <h1 class="text-xl font-bold mb-1">## Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-subtext0 text-xs mb-6">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-subtext0">
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-bold text-text mb-2">### What we collect</h2>
        <p>DearSQL collects minimal data:</p>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 ml-2">
          <li>- <span class="text-text">Bug reports</span> — submitted voluntarily via the "report bug" form. Processed by Sentry. Includes your description and any screenshots you attach.</li>
          <li>- <span class="text-text">License validation</span> — when you activate a Pro license, your license key and a device identifier are sent to Polar.sh to verify the activation. We do not store this on our own servers.</li>
          <li>- <span class="text-text">Purchase data</span> — handled entirely by Polar.sh. We receive your email address when you buy a license. We do not store payment details.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-bold text-text mb-2">### What we don't collect</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-1 ml-2">
          <li>- No analytics or tracking on this website</li>
          <li>- No telemetry from the desktop app</li>
          <li>- No access to your database credentials or query data</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-bold text-text mb-2">### Third-party services</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-1 ml-2">
          <li>- <a href="https://sentry.io" target="_blank">Sentry</a> — error and bug report processing</li>
          <li>- <a href="https://polar.sh" target="_blank">Polar.sh</a> — payment and license management</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">Each service has its own privacy policy governing data they collect.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-bold text-text mb-2">### Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions? <a href="mailto:bing@db99.dev">bing@db99.dev</a></p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="border-t border-surface1 py-4 px-4 text-xs text-subtext0">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto flex flex-wrap items-center justify-between gap-y-2">
      <p>&copy; {currentYear} DearSQL</p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-3 gap-y-1">
        [<a href="/" class="hover:text-text">home</a>]
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        [<a href="/privacy" class="hover:text-text">privacy</a>]
        [<a href="/terms" class="hover:text-text">terms</a>]
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>
